==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jamesonite
<hw>Ja"me*son*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<person>Prof. <etsep>Jameson</etsep></person>, of Edinburgh.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A steel-gray mineral, of metallic luster,
commonly fibrous massive. It is a sulphide of antimony and lead, with a
little iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>James's powder</ent>⟦br⟧
